    "extras": [
      "May to September is the sweet spot: rivers are full, buses run more frequently and Herzegovina is sunny without the worst midsummer heat spikes outside July and August.",
      "Sarajevo and Mostar are easy by bus, but a one- or two-day rental car pays off if you want to combine Jajce, Blagaj, Kravica and Trebinje without long waits between regional departures.",
      "Carry small cash for museum tickets, monastery donations and riverside restaurants, especially in Blagaj, Jajce and Trebinje.",
      "Mostar and Blagaj can feel very hot in mid-afternoon summer sun, so plan bridges, tekija and waterfall stops early or late in the day.",
      "If you are flying out, Trebinje also works well as a final stop before Dubrovnik Airport, but keep border-crossing time in mind."
    ],
